ld. I never should have shut Judie out. Her mother insisted Judie fly to California to be with her. And Judie went, and attempted to commit suicide. Her mother found her in the car in her garage. Judie was then in a coma and wasn't expected to survive. If she did, she would have permanent brain damage. I flew to California along with her best friend. She had given her EQ account away, she even gave away her laptop. She was giving things away left and right that I should have known. But instead I chose to be blind and ignore the situation.....<br>Judie's whole family was with her when she passed. She was pronounced brain dead a few minutes pass 10 that evening.<br><br>I will always be hurt by the death of my son, but more so by the death of my best friend, my soulmate. I wish I had paid a little more attention to her. <br><br>I ask any of you to please post a link to this topic on the UGoD board so all her friends would know what happened with her. I thank all you kind people here on Drinal for making her time online a happy one. She loved Heart of the Hunter very much, which she created with some wonderful friends that she met. I know she deeply cared for Jen/Torrasu who she spoke of in numerous occasions, and was even thinking/looking to buy a house in Utah to be closer to her. She loved alot about this server. She loved the people who were friends with her and dear to her. Shadowcasta, she mentioned you a few times and I know she had alot of fun being your in-game wife. Arclite, Lottor, Dollop, Suntzus, Aenaan, Xion, Pwint, Horudan, Groller, Seke...I'm sure the list goes on and on.....There were so many people she had mentioned in her time with me but I'm sorry to say, I don't remember everyone.  She had, at one point even made characters on my server, just to be closer to me. As I sit here in our home, I miss her laughter, her silliness. The warmth she would bring in everyone's life. I will miss it all. I will miss Judie, and I will always love her very much.<br><br>Her friend had mentioned to me about a memorial ceremony on Drinal for her. If anyone can actually plan one for her, that would be so great, and I would like to attend if possible. Please email me at bkandjw@hotmail.com<br><br>Thank you everyone <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub28.ezboard.com/ueqwolfran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>EQWolfran</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.seaforthlanding.com/images/misc/doom_anm.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Man on the moon?</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/4/02 3:34:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub28.ezboard.com/fdrinal28133frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2370.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.seaforthlanding.com/images/misc/shaman.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: In Memory of Alya.....</span><hr size=1> /mourn...<br><br>Posting a link to this on White Wind's message board.  Will get to UGoD if no one beats me.  Didn't know her well, but know many that did.<br><br>Speechless... <p><font color=white><table bgcolor=#000033>  <tr>    <td>      <img src="http://www.seaforth.com/images/misc/flsh_anm.gif">   </td>   <td><hr>      <center><table bgcolor=#000033><tr><td><img src="http://www.seaforthlanding.com/images/misc/expl_anm.gif"></td><td STYLE="filter: GLOW(color=#008080,strength=#+3)"><center><font size=4>Wolfran Spiritwalker</font><br>51 Barbarian Mystic<br>Spiritual Guide of White Wind<br>Drinal Server</font></center></td><td><img src="http://www.seaforthlanding.com/imag